1
00:00:01,070 --> 00:00:04,100
(theme music)

2
00:00:04,100 --> 00:01:33,050
♪

3
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:38,130
In our last episode
at Shishio's Edo fortress,

4
00:01:38,130 --> 00:01:41,090
Sojiro informed his master
that Kenshin and Saito

5
00:01:41,090 --> 00:01:42,290
were on their
way towards Edo

6
00:01:42,290 --> 00:01:44,270
and would be
arriving shortly.

7
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:46,250
As Shishio
relaxed in his spa,

8
00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:48,260
he and the paramour Ayumi

9
00:01:48,260 --> 00:01:50,230
made plans for their
guests' arrival

10
00:01:50,230 --> 00:01:52,230
and talked about how
to best take advantage

11
00:01:52,230 --> 00:01:54,130
of the situation.

12
00:01:54,130 --> 00:01:55,180
Knowing that Kenshin

13
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:57,150
is one of Japan's
greatest swordsmen

14
00:01:57,150 --> 00:02:00,060
and that a confrontation
with him is inevitable,

15
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:03,130
Shishio wants to find a way
to observe Kenshin in battle

16
00:02:03,130 --> 00:02:06,070
in order to learn his
strengths and weaknesses.

17
00:02:06,070 --> 00:02:08,240
With Ayumi's help
and Sojiro's input,

18
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:11,250
Shishio comes up with a
scheme to achieve this goal.

19
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:14,270
He decides to use his
most ferocious assassin,

20
00:02:14,270 --> 00:02:17,100
the brutal giant Senkaku.

21
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:22,100
♪

22
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,160
(footsteps)

23
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:30,000
♪

24
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,100
Ah, Mr. Himura, Mr. Saito,

25
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:34,120
I am Sojiro, welcome.

26
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:36,040
I know that voice.

27
00:02:37,250 --> 00:02:40,010
Those who betray
my master, Shishio,

28
00:02:40,010 --> 00:02:42,120
don't stay alive
for very long.

29
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,160
♪

30
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:46,130
Be very careful, Saito.

31
00:02:46,130 --> 00:02:49,000
This is the guy who
killed Sir Okubo.

32
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:52,260
Oh, come now,
me, an assassin?

33
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:54,100
I'm just a guide.

34
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:56,210
A sword would be too
heavy for me to carry.

35
00:02:56,210 --> 00:02:59,010
(chuckling)

36
00:02:59,010 --> 00:03:00,130
My master knows
you're here

37
00:03:00,130 --> 00:03:02,080
and is waiting inside.

38
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:04,240
Welcome to Edo.

39
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:07,190
If this is a trap, there's
not much we can do about it.

40
00:03:07,190 --> 00:03:09,170
Come on.

41
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:34,250
♪

42
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:36,170
Eiji, wait.

43
00:03:36,170 --> 00:03:38,290
I can take care of myself,
just leave me alone!

44
00:03:38,290 --> 00:03:40,130
You can't go in there.

45
00:03:40,130 --> 00:03:41,200
But I have to.

46
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,170
Senkaku killed my family.

47
00:03:43,170 --> 00:03:45,140
He murdered them
in cold blood.

48
00:03:45,140 --> 00:03:46,290
My poor parents
and my brother

49
00:03:46,290 --> 00:03:49,000
were innocent and they
hadn't done anything wrong,

50
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,010
but he killed
them anyway.

51
00:03:51,010 --> 00:03:53,110
♪

52
00:03:53,110 --> 00:03:55,040
It's up to me now

53
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:57,140
to avenge all
their deaths.

54
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:59,070
I know how you feel,

55
00:03:59,070 --> 00:04:00,230
but this fortress
is protected

56
00:04:00,230 --> 00:04:03,030
by a whole division
of Shishio's ninjas.

57
00:04:03,030 --> 00:04:05,030
If you go in there
without any plan,

58
00:04:05,030 --> 00:04:06,080
you'll end up
getting captured

59
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,180
and probably tortured.

60
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:10,020
You'll never find
Senkaku that way.

61
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:12,070
Well, I can't just stand
here and do nothing.

62
00:04:12,070 --> 00:04:14,070
I've got to avenge
their deaths.

63
00:04:14,070 --> 00:04:16,150
You just leave everything
to me, all right?

64
00:04:16,150 --> 00:04:18,010
I've never told
you this before,

65
00:04:18,010 --> 00:04:19,220
but I was a member
of the Oni gang.

66
00:04:19,220 --> 00:04:20,250
The Oni?

67
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:22,060
Wabanshu?

68
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:25,060
Yeah, let me
just show you.

69
00:04:25,060 --> 00:04:27,040
(owl hooting)

70
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,130
What are you
gonna do with that?

71
00:04:33,130 --> 00:04:35,260
Just wait for my signal,
then follow me, all right?

72
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:37,020
Huh?

73
00:04:37,020 --> 00:04:38,080
Uh!

74
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:40,160
(whooshing)

75
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:42,290
What was that?

76
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:45,060
Search the grounds!

77
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:46,110
Come on!

78
00:04:48,220 --> 00:04:50,190
(yelling)

79
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,100
Shh!

80
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:56,190
-See anyone?
-Not yet, sir.

81
00:04:56,190 --> 00:04:58,030
It was probably an owl.

82
00:04:58,030 --> 00:05:00,000
Great, now we can
sneak in behind them.

83
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,140
Cool.

84
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:04,090
(grunting)

85
00:05:04,090 --> 00:05:12,290
♪

86
00:05:12,290 --> 00:05:14,230
Would you like a
cool drink, Shishio,

87
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:16,150
it's quite refreshing.

88
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:17,170
They've come.

89
00:05:17,170 --> 00:05:22,000
♪

90
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,010
Your name is Shishio
Makoto, I'm told.

91
00:05:25,010 --> 00:05:28,290
Hmm, most strangers
call me Mr. Makoto.

92
00:05:28,290 --> 00:05:31,140
Some would say
you're impolite.

93
00:05:31,140 --> 00:05:32,260
They might at that.

94
00:05:32,260 --> 00:05:35,010
People say a lot
of things about me.

95
00:05:35,010 --> 00:05:36,030
You better be careful.

96
00:05:36,030 --> 00:05:38,220
It sounds like things
are heating up already.

97
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:40,060
If given a good
enough reason,

98
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:42,160
Kenshin could kill him with
one stroke of his sword.

99
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,290
I don't think he'll try.

100
00:05:43,290 --> 00:05:46,080
As an invited guest
in his enemy's home,

101
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:49,280
he's too honorable to pull
a sneak attack unlike you.

102
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:52,010
Hmm.

103
00:05:52,010 --> 00:05:54,050
What did you attack
the village for?

104
00:05:54,050 --> 00:05:56,030
Your goal is
national domination,

105
00:05:56,030 --> 00:05:57,220
your target Japan itself,

106
00:05:57,220 --> 00:06:00,000
why concern yourself
with a small village?

107
00:06:01,290 --> 00:06:03,040
Hot springs.

108
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,150
Huh?

109
00:06:04,150 --> 00:06:07,200
♪

110
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,280
There are therapeutic
minerals in the water here

111
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:12,100
that help soothe
the pain of my burns.

112
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:14,040
But if I were to allow
other guests here,

113
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:16,050
they would see me and
it would frighten them

114
00:06:16,050 --> 00:06:19,050
so I made it my
own private spa.

115
00:06:19,050 --> 00:06:21,090
You destroyed
an entire village

116
00:06:21,090 --> 00:06:23,180
just because you like
to use its hot springs?

117
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:25,180
(laughing)

118
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:31,000
♪

119
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,280
I'm kidding,
I'm just kidding.

120
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:35,170
Know what your
problem is, Himura?

121
00:06:35,170 --> 00:06:37,230
You don't have
a sense of humor.

122
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,090
And I suppose you do?

123
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:42,040
You're about as funny as a
pile of dead maggots, friend.

124
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:44,040
(gasping)

125
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,270
Hey, be quiet!

126
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:47,240
(owl hooting)

127
00:06:51,130 --> 00:06:54,100
-Why, you, I oughta.
-It won't happen again.

128
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:57,060
They say if you sneeze,
someone's talking about you.

129
00:06:57,060 --> 00:06:59,130
Oh, I hope it's Aoshi.

130
00:06:59,130 --> 00:07:02,070
I took this village because
I needed a military base

131
00:07:02,070 --> 00:07:05,120
to control the
surrounding area.

132
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:07,220
The hot springs turned
out to be a bonus.

133
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:09,140
Bastard.

134
00:07:09,140 --> 00:07:11,270
Not just yet,
my friend.

135
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:13,270
Now let me get
this straight.

136
00:07:13,270 --> 00:07:15,210
You're gonna use
this fort as a base

137
00:07:15,210 --> 00:07:17,170
while trying to
topple the government?

138
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:19,220
Mr. Saito, I remember
when you were captain

139
00:07:19,220 --> 00:07:21,090
of the Shinsengumi.

140
00:07:21,090 --> 00:07:24,000
I have so much more in common
with you than Mr. Himura,

141
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,190
I thought you'd
understand my intentions.

142
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:28,080
I guess I was wrong.

143
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:30,280
-Go on.
-Ten years ago,

144
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:32,240
when Mr. Himura was
still remembered

145
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:34,160
as Battousai the Slasher,

146
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:38,210
I succeeded him as the
government's shadow assassin.

147
00:07:38,210 --> 00:07:39,270
I was their
loyal servant,

148
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:42,250
I worked hard,
obeyed every command.

149
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,290
But I learned more
with each new assignment

150
00:07:46,290 --> 00:07:49,120
until I knew so many of
the government's secrets

151
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,090
that they decided to
protect themselves

152
00:07:51,090 --> 00:07:54,040
by having me eliminated.

153
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:56,000
(guns firing)

154
00:07:56,000 --> 00:08:01,140
♪

155
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:05,120
They set me on fire to
make sure I was dead.

156
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:07,120
(screaming)

157
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:11,190
Almost every inch of
my body was charred,

158
00:08:11,190 --> 00:08:14,150
but my anger within grew
hotter than the flames

159
00:08:14,150 --> 00:08:16,120
and that kept me alive.

160
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:18,210
Now I carry that
heat with me,

161
00:08:18,210 --> 00:08:20,130
a heat so intense,

162
00:08:20,130 --> 00:08:22,150
it would be unbearable
to living things

163
00:08:22,150 --> 00:08:26,140
if I didn't keep
it under control.

164
00:08:26,140 --> 00:08:28,040
It's like a
reminder of hell

165
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:32,000
still burning inside me.

166
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:35,080
I'll have my
revenge someday.

167
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,260
Waiting will
make it sweeter.

168
00:08:37,260 --> 00:08:39,000
In a strange way,

169
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,050
I appreciate what
they did to me.

170
00:08:42,050 --> 00:08:43,090
These wounds
have taught me

171
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:44,250
my life's most
important lessons,

172
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:46,280
which are now
ingrained within my heart.

173
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:49,010
If I trust, I'll be betrayed,

174
00:08:49,010 --> 00:08:51,060
if I let down my
guard, I'll be killed,

175
00:08:51,060 --> 00:08:55,120
I can protect my life only by
taking the lives of others,

176
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,220
and that a desirable man

177
00:08:56,220 --> 00:08:59,040
will remain no
matter what happens

178
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:01,110
and he will attract
beautiful women

179
00:09:01,110 --> 00:09:02,220
all his life.

180
00:09:02,220 --> 00:09:04,160
(chuckling)

181
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:06,120
Well, then sounds to me
like you've got it made.

182
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:08,000
Why don't you
just stay here?

183
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,110
Believe me, I'm tired of
having to track you down.

184
00:09:10,110 --> 00:09:12,180
It'd make my job
a whole lot easier.

185
00:09:12,180 --> 00:09:14,230
I'm confused,
truly I am.

186
00:09:14,230 --> 00:09:17,130
We all lived through the
end of the Tokugawa Era.

187
00:09:17,130 --> 00:09:19,140
I simply don't understand.

188
00:09:19,140 --> 00:09:21,150
♪

189
00:09:21,150 --> 00:09:24,130
What is it that made
you so different from me?

190
00:09:24,130 --> 00:09:26,240
♪

191
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,190
The end of the
Tokugawa Shogunate

192
00:09:28,190 --> 00:09:30,050
was a disaster.

193
00:09:30,050 --> 00:09:33,040
The entire country was in
danger of falling apart.

194
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:35,010
Civil war raged everywhere,

195
00:09:35,010 --> 00:09:37,030
in the countryside
and in the cities,

196
00:09:37,030 --> 00:09:39,130
between the royalist
loyal to the Emperor

197
00:09:39,130 --> 00:09:41,250
and those who wanted the
power of the government

198
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:44,100
to remain in the
hands of the Shogun.

199
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:45,290
I'd think that any
man who had witnessed

200
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:49,010
the fear and confusion of
that time would want to see

201
00:09:49,010 --> 00:09:51,060
his country under
control again,

202
00:09:51,060 --> 00:09:54,220
that they would do what was
necessary to reunify Japan.

203
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:58,050
♪

204
00:09:58,050 --> 00:10:02,090
Meanwhile, the government
tried to assassinate me.

205
00:10:02,090 --> 00:10:05,020
By the time I had
recovered from my burns,

206
00:10:05,020 --> 00:10:06,150
the disturbance was over

207
00:10:06,150 --> 00:10:08,260
and the Meiji government
was now in control.

208
00:10:08,260 --> 00:10:10,260
Of course, they
wanted me dead too,

209
00:10:10,260 --> 00:10:13,240
but the Meiji government
was too weak to get it done.

210
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:17,020
Can a country be run by a
government as weak as that?

211
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:18,240
No!

212
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:21,250
♪

213
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:23,120
Mediocrity
and complacency

214
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,140
cannot be allowed
to rule Japan.

215
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:28,000
I'll make the
country strong again.

216
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,000
Total and supreme
control will be mine alone!

217
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:34,030
Now do you understand the
righteousness of my destiny?

218
00:10:34,030 --> 00:10:36,100
♪

219
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,060
But what about the
people who don't care

220
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:40,000
if you're right or wrong,

221
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,230
who want to live peacefully?

222
00:10:41,230 --> 00:10:44,230
Their pain for your
ambition with their blood.

223
00:10:44,230 --> 00:10:48,230
♪

224
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:52,020
Survival of the fittest,
life's most basic law.

225
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:55,080
The righteousness of
my path is undeniable.

226
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:57,160
I'm stubborn, I guess,

227
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:59,290
because I don't believe
it for one second,

228
00:10:59,290 --> 00:11:01,180
and I can't let
innocent people

229
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:03,050
go on dying
because of you.

230
00:11:03,050 --> 00:11:04,230
Got it?

231
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:07,250
So, Mr. Saito,
what about you?

232
00:11:07,250 --> 00:11:09,100
Well, now.

233
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:12,160
The way I feel has nothing
to do with such noble ideas.

234
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:13,210
It's very simple.

235
00:11:13,210 --> 00:11:15,140
I'd just feel a whole
lot more comfortable

236
00:11:15,140 --> 00:11:16,270
without Shishio around.

237
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:18,030
If it's a
fight you want,

238
00:11:18,030 --> 00:11:19,280
then it's a
fight you'll get.

239
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,190
But I don't think
we should rush to get

240
00:11:21,190 --> 00:11:23,160
to the main
event quite yet.

241
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:27,080
First, there's someone
I'd like you to meet.

242
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,190
Huh?

243
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:32,030
I was the one
responsible

244
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:34,110
for destroying the
Shingetsu Village.

245
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:42,190
♪

246
00:11:42,190 --> 00:11:43,250
(chuckling)

247
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:46,160
Gentlemen, may I
introduce Mr. Senkaku?

248
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:49,000
If you're responsible for the
destruction of the village,

249
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:52,130
then you're the one who
murdered Eiji's parents.

250
00:11:52,130 --> 00:11:53,280
So what, punk?

251
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,100
You're dead!

252
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:56,040
Ya!

253
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:57,080
He's quick.

254
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:58,180
You've had it!

255
00:11:58,180 --> 00:12:00,000
(yelling)

256
00:12:01,270 --> 00:12:03,280
(laughing)

257
00:12:05,090 --> 00:12:08,130
Poor man, I thought he'd
last longer than that.

258
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:09,120
Hey, you can go ahead

259
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:11,220
and stick a fork in
this guy, he's done.

260
00:12:11,220 --> 00:12:13,110
I promised Eiji.

261
00:12:13,110 --> 00:12:15,270
Hmm?

262
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:18,250
♪

263
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:20,150
(grunting)

264
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:22,020
(gasping)

265
00:12:22,020 --> 00:12:23,150
You then your boss,

266
00:12:23,150 --> 00:12:25,070
that's what I
promised him.

267
00:12:25,070 --> 00:12:27,210
♪

268
00:12:29,210 --> 00:12:32,170
♪

269
00:12:32,170 --> 00:12:35,000
You're history,
dead meat kid!

270
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:38,240
♪

271
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:41,090
-Yeah?
