272
00:12:41,090 --> 00:12:43,040
I killed 99 men so far

273
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:45,150
and they're all a lot
stronger than you.

274
00:12:45,150 --> 00:12:48,120
You'll make it
an even 100.

275
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:50,170
(yelling)

276
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:53,120
♪

277
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:55,010
Ninety-nine people.

278
00:12:55,010 --> 00:12:57,220
Hmm, that is an
awful lot of people.

279
00:12:57,220 --> 00:12:59,070
(yelling)

280
00:12:59,070 --> 00:13:05,020
♪

281
00:13:05,020 --> 00:13:05,981
Whoa.

282
00:13:05,981 --> 00:13:08,110
Kenshin is as
quick as people say.

283
00:13:08,110 --> 00:13:09,160
But when it
comes to speed,

284
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:12,030
there isn't anybody
who can match Senkaku.

285
00:13:12,030 --> 00:13:16,020
♪

286
00:13:16,020 --> 00:13:17,040
Now die!

287
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:19,140
(yelling)

288
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,140
Wow.

289
00:13:22,140 --> 00:13:23,150
Hey.

290
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:25,250
Is that the only thing
you know how to do?

291
00:13:25,250 --> 00:13:27,160
Anybody who was
fast on his feet

292
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:29,290
could slip around
behind his opponent.

293
00:13:29,290 --> 00:13:32,070
Even someone who's...

294
00:13:32,070 --> 00:13:34,130
...a really big
guy like me.

295
00:13:36,030 --> 00:13:37,210
We're equally quick,

296
00:13:37,210 --> 00:13:40,050
but I also have physical
strength and stamina

297
00:13:40,050 --> 00:13:41,190
you can't hope to match.

298
00:13:41,190 --> 00:13:44,150
My crescent blades will slice
you into pieces so small,

299
00:13:44,150 --> 00:13:46,270
there won't be enough
left of you to bury!

300
00:13:46,270 --> 00:13:49,180
(yelling)

301
00:13:49,180 --> 00:13:58,030
♪

302
00:13:58,030 --> 00:14:00,250
(grunting)

303
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:02,290
♪

304
00:14:02,290 --> 00:14:06,040
(grunting)

305
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:14,010
♪

306
00:14:15,170 --> 00:14:17,140
(owl hooting)

307
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:24,140
Whoa.

308
00:14:24,140 --> 00:14:26,250
Their security's a lot
tougher than I thought.

309
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:29,140
There's gotta be a
way to get in there.

310
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:30,150
Got to,

311
00:14:30,150 --> 00:14:32,290
otherwise I'll
never find Senkaku.

312
00:14:32,290 --> 00:14:34,240
Don't worry,
I'll find a way.

313
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:37,030
Sneaking into places is
one of the specialties

314
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:39,200
of the Oni gang so
it'll be easy for me

315
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:41,190
'cause I'm not
scared of anything,

316
00:14:41,190 --> 00:14:42,240
except for...

317
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:45,070
...big, hairy spiders!

318
00:14:45,070 --> 00:14:47,190
Misao, quiet!

319
00:14:47,190 --> 00:14:49,200
What was that?

320
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:51,170
What are you scared of?

321
00:14:51,170 --> 00:14:53,100
(squealing)

322
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,100
Spider?

323
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:57,020
There's someone
in the woods.

324
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:59,170
That's just great, now
we're gonna get caught.

325
00:14:59,170 --> 00:15:01,150
My one weakness, I
don't like spiders,

326
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:02,220
what can I say?

327
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:05,080
How does "Sorry I got
you killed" sound?

328
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:07,090
Who are you?

329
00:15:07,090 --> 00:15:08,250
Come on out!

330
00:15:10,170 --> 00:15:12,220
Guess I'll have
to give myself up.

331
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:14,150
(audible sigh)

332
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:16,150
You stay here and
don't make a sound.

333
00:15:16,150 --> 00:15:17,220
Huh?

334
00:15:17,220 --> 00:15:20,050
♪

335
00:15:20,050 --> 00:15:23,070
So, just what the hell
is your name anyway?

336
00:15:23,070 --> 00:15:25,040
I'm Misao Makimachi,

337
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:27,180
but I don't give
just anybody my name.

338
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:29,210
Just try to find
out who I am.

339
00:15:29,210 --> 00:15:31,030
Huh?

340
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:33,240
Uh, she just told
us her name, right?

341
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:35,270
Smart, she ain't.

342
00:15:35,270 --> 00:15:38,200
I'm so embarrassed, oh.

343
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,150
How could I do that?

344
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:43,050
I don't care,
I really don't.

345
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:44,280
Now, all of you,
out of my way!

346
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:46,250
I said, "Back off,

347
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:48,140
or you're gonna get hurt!"

348
00:15:48,140 --> 00:15:49,200
Is this some
kind of joke?

349
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:51,220
She just must be a fool.

350
00:15:51,220 --> 00:15:52,230
Men, take her out!

351
00:15:52,230 --> 00:15:54,070
(shouting)

352
00:15:54,070 --> 00:15:56,080
The joke's on you, sucker!

353
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:58,060
(shouting)

354
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:00,190
So who's the fool now?

355
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:03,170
(grunting)

356
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:12,260
♪

357
00:16:12,260 --> 00:16:14,140
Ah.

358
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:18,180
(smacking)

359
00:16:21,090 --> 00:16:23,260
Ha, some punch line, huh?

360
00:16:23,260 --> 00:16:25,060
Stop it!

361
00:16:25,060 --> 00:16:26,110
Huh?

362
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:29,040
Eiji?

363
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:30,100
Oh.

364
00:16:31,260 --> 00:16:33,250
You're gonna
be our guide.

365
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:36,190
Sneak us inside or
you're dead meat, get it?

366
00:16:36,190 --> 00:16:38,030
But you're just a kid.

367
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:40,110
I'll bet that you've
never killed anybody,

368
00:16:40,110 --> 00:16:43,070
and I'll bet you you
can't kill me either.

369
00:16:43,070 --> 00:16:45,140
That's it, you're history.

370
00:16:45,140 --> 00:16:47,010
Wait!

371
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:52,020
Take us inside
right now or you die.

372
00:16:52,020 --> 00:16:54,060
Just calm down, kid.

373
00:16:54,060 --> 00:16:56,100
I promise to do whatever
you say, all right?

374
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:58,120
(yelling)

375
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:00,170
(grunting)

376
00:17:00,170 --> 00:17:10,150
♪

377
00:17:10,150 --> 00:17:12,140
Keep running, you
little cockroach!

378
00:17:12,140 --> 00:17:14,030
You can't keep
running forever,

379
00:17:14,030 --> 00:17:15,210
I'll catch you
sooner or later,

380
00:17:15,210 --> 00:17:18,180
and when I do, I'll
slice you into confetti!

381
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:23,100
(yelling)

382
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:24,200
Well, now.

383
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:27,010
Looks like Mr. Himura's
getting pushed to his limit

384
00:17:27,010 --> 00:17:28,150
and he's not pushing back.

385
00:17:28,150 --> 00:17:29,220
Aren't you going
to help him out?

386
00:17:29,220 --> 00:17:32,040
No way, I wouldn't want
to show him all my tricks,

387
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:35,240
and besides, I don't think
he'd appreciate the help.

388
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:37,160
You'll see.

389
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:39,170
♪

390
00:17:39,170 --> 00:17:41,100
Shishio looked a
hell of a lot happier

391
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:43,220
before this fight started.

392
00:17:43,220 --> 00:17:46,130
He looks a lot
more serious now.

393
00:17:46,130 --> 00:17:48,190
He's trying to understand
Kenshin's technique,

394
00:17:48,190 --> 00:17:50,270
but he hasn't
quite got it yet.

395
00:17:50,270 --> 00:17:52,220
But he'll understand
soon enough.

396
00:17:52,220 --> 00:17:54,250
(grunting)

397
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:57,040
See how Shishio
watches him?

398
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:59,080
And Kenshin knows that his
strengths and weaknesses

399
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:00,150
are being assessed,

400
00:18:00,150 --> 00:18:03,020
and that's why he's chosen
the self-destruct defense.

401
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:04,180
It gives away nothing.

402
00:18:04,180 --> 00:18:06,030
Self-destruct?

403
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:10,120
It should be soon.

404
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:14,110
All right, that's it!

405
00:18:14,110 --> 00:18:16,030
(grunting)

406
00:18:16,030 --> 00:18:18,030
(screaming)

407
00:18:18,030 --> 00:18:23,260
♪

408
00:18:23,260 --> 00:18:26,100
(gasping)

409
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:29,150
(groaning)

410
00:18:29,150 --> 00:18:33,010
It's--it's my leg,
I can't move it, ahh!

411
00:18:33,010 --> 00:18:34,210
Ahh!

412
00:18:34,210 --> 00:18:37,100
Moving that quickly for that
long pushed the thigh muscle

413
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,230
into a state of hypertension

414
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:40,280
which overloaded the
bone until it broke,

415
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:43,020
that's what caused
you to self-destruct.

416
00:18:43,020 --> 00:18:46,090
Nonsense, we were both moving
at about the same speed!

417
00:18:46,090 --> 00:18:47,130
My physique is perfect,

418
00:18:47,130 --> 00:18:49,040
there's no way I could've
pushed my body beyond

419
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:50,270
its limits just
by chasing you.

420
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:52,180
You're muscular, all right.

421
00:18:52,180 --> 00:18:53,200
You're so overdeveloped

422
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:55,060
that when you used
your full strength,

423
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:57,030
your bones couldn't
handle the overload.

424
00:18:57,030 --> 00:18:59,170
No, no way!

425
00:18:59,170 --> 00:19:02,020
Nothing like this has
ever happened to me before.

426
00:19:02,020 --> 00:19:03,140
It can't be!

427
00:19:03,140 --> 00:19:04,190
It must be a trick.

428
00:19:04,190 --> 00:19:06,100
Tell me, how the hell
did you do this to me?

429
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:08,210
You still don't
get it, do you?

430
00:19:08,210 --> 00:19:10,120
It's a trick, right?

431
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:12,040
Well, some might
call it that.

432
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:14,090
Actually, you tricked
yourself by following

433
00:19:14,090 --> 00:19:15,270
Mr. Himura so closely.

434
00:19:15,270 --> 00:19:17,200
He sped up every time
he got behind you

435
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:19,070
and you sped up with him.

436
00:19:19,070 --> 00:19:22,080
And he kept making you
turn the same way each time.

437
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:23,140
The turning did it.

438
00:19:23,140 --> 00:19:25,020
How?

439
00:19:25,020 --> 00:19:27,220
You used the same leg
to turn with every time

440
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:31,050
until the bone couldn't
take it and self-destructed.

441
00:19:31,050 --> 00:19:32,170
Ah.

442
00:19:32,170 --> 00:19:36,100
These new fighting techniques
are really quite fascinating.

443
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:37,220
Huh?

444
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:40,220
♪

445
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:43,020
I haven't really
killed 99 men.

446
00:19:43,020 --> 00:19:45,010
That was all
a lie, honest.

447
00:19:45,010 --> 00:19:46,160
I've only killed
about a dozen men

448
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:47,230
